cs.HC, cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.MM, cs.LG. 

The paper focuses on a new concept in the field of human-computer interaction, specifically soft user interfaces that facilitate touch interaction through deformation. This falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also uses statistical learning algorithms based on convolutional neural networks to map deformations from human touch to categorical labels and touch location, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The device used in the study also involves robotics (cs.RO) and multimedia (cs.MM) as it is used to control a game.
